claim.claim-text:
A method for constructing a set of Zero-Correlation-Zone (ZCZ) Concatenated Complementary Pair (CCP) sequences of length L×N with zero-correlation-zone range equal to one and set size greater than two, for use in a communication system (900) the method comprising:
selecting (804, 1404) sequences A (504) and B (506) of length N that form a complementary pair (502);
selecting (806) a set (508) of more than two pairs of sign sequences pAi and pBi of length L/2; which satisfy the conditions:
(i) the sign sequence pAi is uncorrelated with the sign sequence pBi at lag=0 and at lag=-1, and
(ii) the sum of the cross-correlation of the sign sequence pAi with the sign sequence pAj and the cross-correlation of the sign sequence pBi with the sign sequence pBj is equal to zero at lag=0 for sign sequences of a set member i and a different set member j;
for each member i of the set of ZCZ CCP sequences:
combining (808, 1410, 518, 518') the sign sequences pAi and pBi with the complementary pair sequences A and B, respectively, to form the member ZCZ CCP sequence (520), and
selecting one or more sequences of the set of sequences for use in a transceiver of the communication system,
where the ZCZ CCP sequences facilitate communication.

The method of claim 1, wherein the set size is 2M, where selecting a set of more than two pairs of sign sequences comprises:
selecting M sign sequences {pi} of length L such the sequences S1i=p0i⁢A,p1i⁢B,p2i⁢A,…,pL-2i⁢A,pL-1i⁢B,i=0,1,…,M-1 are ZCZ CCP sequences;
reversing and conjugating the sequence A to produce the sequence A*;
reversing and conjugating the sequence B to produce the sequence B*; and
forming the M sign sequences S2i=±p0i⁢-B←*,p1i⁢A←*,p2i⁢-B←*,…,pL-2i⁢-B←*,pL-1i⁢A←*,i=0,1,…,M-1;

where the set of ZCZ CCP sequences comprise the M sequences S1i and the M sequences S2i.

The transceiver sub-system of claim 9, where the transceiver sub-system is operable to identify a propagated training sequence of the set of training sequences, the transceiver sub-system further comprising:
a receiver (904);
at least one second ZCZ CCP sequence generator (500"'), each operable to generate a second ZCZ CCP sequence;
a first correlator (914), operable to produce a first cross-correlation between the first ZCZ CCP sequence and the propagated training sequence;
at least one second correlator (918), each operable to produce a second cross-correlation between a sequence of the at least one second ZCZ CCP sequence and the propagated training sequence; and
a comparator (922), operable to identify the transmitted training sequence by comparing the first cross-correlation and the at least one second cross-correlation.

The transceiver sub-system of claim 10, where:
the first ZCZ CCP sequence comprises comprising a plurality of concatenated sub-sequences, each sub-sequence being a sequence A of a complementary pair modulated by a sign of a first sign sequence pAi, concatenated with a sequence B of the complementary pair modulated by a sign of a second sign sequence pBi;
the second ZCZ CCP sequence comprises a plurality of concatenated sub-sequences, each sub-sequence being the sequence A of the complementary pair modulated by a sign of a third sign sequence pAj, concatenated with the sequence B of the complementary pair modulated by a sign of a fourth sign sequence pBj;
the first, second, third and fourth sign sequences satisfy a first condition that:
the first sign sequence pAj is uncorrelated with the second sign sequence pBi at lag 0 and at lag = -1; and
each of the at least one third sign sequence pAj is uncorrelated with the fourth sign sequence pBj at lag 0 and at lag = -1; and
the first, second, third and fourth sign sequences satisfy a second condition that:
the first sign sequence pAi is uncorrelated with each of the at least one third sign sequence pAj at lag 0;
the second sign sequence pBi is uncorrelated with each of the at least one fourth sign sequence pBj at lag 0;
the cross-correlation of the first sign sequence pAi with each of the at least one fourth sign sequence pBj is zero at lag=0 and at lag=-1; and
the cross-correlation of the second sign sequence pBi with the each of the at least one third sign sequence pAj is zero at lag=0 and at lag=1.

The transceiver sub-system of claim 13, where
the training sequence of the set of training sequences comprises a plurality of concatenated sub-sequences, each sub-sequence being a sequence A of a complementary pair modulated by a sign of a first sign sequence pAi, concatenated with a sequence B of the complementary pair modulated by a sign of a second sign sequence pBi; and
the set of training sequences comprises: the first ZCZ CCP sequence; and at least two second sequence comprising a plurality of concatenated sub-sequences, each sub-sequence being the sequence A of the complementary pair modulated by a sign of a third sign sequence pAj, concatenated with the sequence B of the complementary pair modulated by a sign of a fourth sign sequence pBj;
